--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1. Overview
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  phpTourney is a PHP script collection consisting of a simple user-system,
  a news-system, a reporting system for matches and of course the tourney logic
  for single- and double-elimination brackets with or without qualification.
  It is released under the GPL - Have a look in LICENSE for details.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  2. Getting started
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  2.1. Requirements
       - Apache Web Server
         (Tested: 1.3.29, 2.0.?)
       - PHP (installed as module)
         (Tested: 4.3.4)
       - MySQL Database Server
         (Tested: 4.0.16)
       - Optional: ImageMagick [for cropping screenshots]
         (Tested: 5.5.7)
       - Optional: SMTP Server [for sending mails]

  2.2. Installation
       - Unpack phpTourney-x.y.z.tar.gz into a directory on your webspace.
       - Make sure that the directories /data/screenshots and /data/serverlists
         and the file /VERSION are writable for the www-user.
       - Execute the SQL-script /sql/phptourney.sql (i.e. with phpMyAdmin)
       - Copy the file /inc/config-default.inc.php to /inc/config.inc.php
         and edit its content to your needs.
       - Log in with admin/password and create sections and seasons...

  2.3. Update
       - When you do an update from a version that only changed in the last digit
         (i.e. 0.8.5 -> 0.8.6) then you can just unzip it over the old installation.
       - In case you want to update from a version that changed in the second digit
         (i.e. 0.8.5 -> 0.9.0) then you should execute the update-procedure by
         visiting the URL http://yourdomain/path/to/phptourney/data/update0.9.0.php
